organisation.about:
The City of London Academy (Southwark) is located in Bermondsey, South London. The school is part of the DfES funded Academy programme, with the City of London as our prime sponsor. We also work closely with our local authority, the London Borough of Southwark.

The Academy is a totally new school for 11-19 year olds. We opened in temporary accommodation in September 2003, and we occupied our permanent facilities in September 2005. The Academy has a full range of teaching accommodation with all attendant support facilities, including separate halls for dining and assembly, a sports hall, and specialist dance and drama studios. We provide pupils from the Bermondsey area and the City of London with a high quality of education, and we currently have almost 1,000 students on roll in Years 7 to 11, and a sixth form of over 200 students.

Our underlying vision is of an Academy based on a culture of high expectation and achievement within a caring community, with a focus on Business & Enterprise and Sport. We also achieved the Artsmark Gold award in 2010 for excellence in the performing, applied and fine arts. The Academy won the Prime Ministerâ€™s Public Building of the Year Award in 2006.

The City of London Academy was one of the first Academy schools, and we have a high profile in the field of secondary education. Our sponsor, the City of London Corporation, provides more than just sponsorship, giving us access to the organisations and businesses in the City. We have close relationships with many city companies and guilds, as well as with the local industries in Bermondsey.
